{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849519728,"sessionID":"ses_28721972bffeZ0Etbv4Q7BbOE4","part":{"id":"prt_d78e13a18001di0qi8XFJDmodn","messageID":"msg_d78df374c001NLEaaaqCoKlP2X","sessionID":"ses_28721972bffeZ0Etbv4Q7BbOE4","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-cd6130246313418bbe8b6eb16e9200be","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/design.md","content":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe Router HTTP reverse proxy core provides session-aware routing for AgentCube sandbox invocations. It resolves sessions via the store, creates new sandboxes through the Workload Manager when needed, reverse-proxies HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints, injects JWT tokens for sandbox authentication, and tracks activity for idle timeout detection.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              AgentCube Cluster                               │\n│  ┌─────────────┐                                                             │\n│  │ Client/SDK  │                                                             │\n│  └──────┬──────┘                                                             │\n│         │ HTTP + x-agentcube-session-id                                      │\n│         ▼                                                                     │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                        Router (pkg/router)                              │ │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  │ │\n│  │  │   Server    │  │SessionManager │  │JWTManager  │  │ ReverseProxy  │  │ │\n│  │  │  (Gin)      │  │               │  │            │  │               │  │ │\n│  │  └──────┬──────┘  └───────┬───────┘  └─────┬──────┘  └───────┬───────┘  │ │\n│  │         │                 │                 │                 │          │ │\n│  │  ┌──────▼─────────────────▼─────────────────▼─────────────────▼──────┐  │ │\n│  │  │                     Middleware Stack                               │  │ │\n│  │  │  Logger → Recovery → ConcurrencyLimit                              │  │ │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │ │\n│  └──────────┬────────────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────┘ │\n│             │                                    │                            │\n│             ▼                                    ▼                            │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐               ┌────────────────────────────┐            │\n│  │  Redis/Valkey    │               │    Workload Manager        │            │\n│  │  (Session Store) │               │    (Sandbox Creation)      │            │\n│  └──────────────────┘               └─────────────┬──────────────┘            │\n│                                                     │                         │\n│                                                     ▼                         │\n│                                      ┌────────────────────────────┐           │\n│                                      │  Kubernetes API Server     │           │\n│                                      │  (CRDs, Pods, Secrets)     │           │\n│                                      └─────────────┬──────────────┘           │\n│                                                    │                          │\n│                                                    ▼                          │\n│                                      ┌────────────────────────────┐           │\n│                                      │      Sandbox Pods          │           │\n│                                      │  (Target Endpoints)        │           │\n│                                      └────────────────────────────┘           │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\n1. Client Request → Router Server\n   │\n2. Middleware Chain (Logger → Recovery → ConcurrencyLimit)\n   │\n3. Route Handler (handleInvoke)\n   │\n4. Session Resolution (SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession)\n   ├─ Header present → Store lookup\n   └─ Header empty → Workload Manager POST → Store save\n   │\n5. Last-Activity Update (store.UpdateSessionLastActivity)\n   │\n6. Entry Point Selection (SandboxInfo.EntryPoints matching)\n   │\n7. JWT Generation (JWTManager.GenerateToken) [for Sandbox/SandboxClaim]\n   │\n8. Reverse Proxy (httputil.ReverseProxy)\n   ├─ Director: path normalization, forwarding headers, JWT\n   └─ ErrorHandler: 502/504 error mapping\n   │\n9. Response Header Injection (x-agentcube-session-id)\n   │\n10. Last-Activity Update (after proxy completion)\n   │\n11. Response → Client\n```\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### Component Relationships\n\n| Component | Role | Dependencies |\n|-----------|------|--------------|\n| `Server` | Gin HTTP server, route registration, lifecycle management | `SessionManager`, `Store`, `JWTManager`, `http.Transport` |\n| `SessionManager` | Session resolution, sandbox creation via Workload Manager | `Store`, Workload Manager HTTP client |\n| `JWTManager` | RS256 JWT generation, K8s Secret persistence | `kubernetes.Interface`, RSA keys |\n| `ReverseProxy` | HTTP forwarding to sandbox pods, header injection | `http.Transport`, `JWTManager` |\n| `Middleware` | Concurrency limiting via semaphore | Config (`MaxConcurrentRequests`) |\n| `Handlers` | Health endpoints, invocation routing | `SessionManager`, `Store`, `ReverseProxy` |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n|---------|---------|-------------|\n| Gin | HTTP framework, routing, middleware | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` |\n| JWT | RS256 JWT signing | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` |\n| HTTP2 | h2c server configuration | `golang.org/x/net/http2` |\n| Client-go | Kubernetes API client | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` |\n| Klog | Structured logging | `k8s.io/klog/v2` |\n| Store | Session storage interface | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` |\n| Types | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` |\n| APIErrors | Kubernetes API status errors | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` |\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Config (`config.go`)\n\n```go\npackage router\n\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string        // Listening port (e.g., \":8080\")\n    EnableTLS             bool          // Enable TLS\n    TLSCert               string        // TLS certificate file path\n    TLSKey                string        // TLS private key file path\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int           // Semaphore capacity (default 1000 when <=0)\n    Debug                 bool          // Gin debug mode\n}\n```\n\n**Defaults:**\n- `Port`: `\":8080\"`\n- `MaxConcurrentRequests`: `1000` (when value <= 0 in `NewServer`)\n\n### Server (`server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config         *Config\n    engine         *gin.Engine\n    httpServer     *http.Server\n    sessionManager SessionManager\n    storeClient    store.Store\n    httpTransport  *http.Transport\n    jwtManager     *JWTManager\n}\n```\n\n**HTTP Server Configuration:**\n- `ReadTimeout`: 30s\n- `IdleTimeout`: 90s\n- H2C enabled via `http2.Server`\n\n### SessionManager (`session_manager.go`)\n\n```go\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\ntype manager struct {\n    storeClient     store.Store\n    workloadMgrAddr string\n    httpClient      *http.Client\n}\n```\n\n**HTTP Client Configuration:**\n- `Timeout`: 2m\n- `MaxIdleConnsPerHost`: 100\n- `DisableCompression`: false\n- HTTP2: `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n\n### JWTManager (`jwt.go`)\n\n```go\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n```\n\n**Constants:**\n```go\nconst (\n    rsaKeySize          = 2048\n    jwtExpiration       = 5 * time.Minute\n    IdentitySecretName  = \"picod-router-identity\"\n    PrivateKeyDataKey   = \"private.pem\"\n    PublicKeyDataKey    = \"public.pem\"\n)\n\nvar IdentityNamespace = \"default\" // init: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE if set\n```\n\n### Error Types (`errors.go`)\n\n```go\ntype SessionNotFoundError struct {\n    SessionID string\n}\n\ntype SandboxUnreachableError struct {\n    SandboxID string\n}\n\ntype SandboxTimeoutError struct {\n    SandboxID string\n}\n\ntype JWTSigningError struct {\n    Err error\n}\n\ntype WorkloadManagerError struct {\n    StatusCode int\n    Message    string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Route Table\n\n| Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n|--------|------|------------|---------|\n| GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n| GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n| GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n| POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n| GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n| POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n\n### Session Manager Interface\n\n```go\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- When `sessionID` is empty: POST to Workload Manager, store result, return `SandboxInfo`\n- When `sessionID` is non-empty: Lookup from store, return `SandboxInfo` or error\n\n**Workload Manager Endpoints:**\n- `AgentRuntime`: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n- `CodeInterpreter`: `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/code-interpreter`\n\n### JWT Manager Interface\n\n```go\nfunc NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)\nfunc (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\nfunc (j *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error\n```\n\n**JWT Claims Structure:**\n```go\n{\n    \"exp\": <now + 5m Unix>,\n    \"iat\": <now Unix>,\n    \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n    // + custom claims (e.g., \"session_id\")\n}\n```\n\n### Health Endpoints\n\n**Live Check (`GET /health/live`):**\n```json\n{\"status\": \"alive\"}\n```\nStatus: 200\n\n**Ready Check (`GET /health/ready`):**\n```json\n{\"status\": \"ready\"}\n```\nStatus: 200 (when sessionManager != nil)\n\n```json\n{\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}\n```\nStatus: 503 (when sessionManager == nil)\n\n### Invocation Response Headers\n\n| Header | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| `x-agentcube-session-id` | Resolved session ID |\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n    \"error\": \"<message>\",\n    \"code\": \"<error_code>\"\n}\n```\n\n**Error Codes:**\n| Code | HTTP Status | Condition |\n|------|-------------|-----------|\n| `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Store lookup failed |\n| `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | 502 | Connection refused |\n| `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | 504 | Timeout during proxy |\n| `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | 500 | JWT generation failed |\n| `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | 429 | Concurrency limit exhausted |\n| `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | 404 | Empty EntryPoints in SandboxInfo |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Proxy Error Mapping (`reverse_proxy.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc proxyErrorHandler(resp http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request, err error) {\n    errMsg := err.Error()\n    var statusCode int\n    var message string\n    \n    if strings.Contains(errMsg, \"connection refused\") {\n        statusCode = http.StatusBadGateway\n        message = \"sandbox unreachable\"\n    } else if strings.Contains(errMsg, \"timeout\") {\n        statusCode = http.StatusGatewayTimeout\n        message = \"sandbox timeout\"\n    } else {\n        statusCode = http.StatusBadGateway\n        message = \"sandbox unreachable\"\n    }\n    \n    resp.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    resp.WriteHeader(statusCode)\n    json.NewEncoder(resp).Encode(gin.H{\"error\": message})\n}\n```\n\n### Handler Error Helper (`handlers.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc handleGetSandboxError(c *gin.Context, err error) {\n    if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        c.JSON(http.StatusNotFound, gin.H{\"error\": err.Error()})\n        return\n    }\n    \n    if apiStatus, ok := err.(apierrors.APIStatus); ok {\n        code := int(apiStatus.Status().Code)\n        if code == 0 {\n            code = http.StatusInternalServerError\n        }\n        msg := apiStatus.Status().Message\n        if msg == \"\" {\n            msg = err.Error()\n        }\n        if code == http.StatusInternalServerError {\n            msg = \"internal server error\"\n        }\n        c.JSON(code, gin.H{\"error\": msg})\n        return\n    }\n    \n    c.JSON(http.StatusInternalServerError, gin.H{\"error\": \"internal server error\"})\n}\n```\n\n### Workload Manager Response Handling\n\n| HTTP Status | Error Type |\n|-------------|------------|\n| 404 | `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError` |\n| Non-200 | `WorkloadManagerError` |\n| Empty `sessionId` in body | Internal error (validation) |\n\n### Store Error Mapping\n\n| Store Error | HTTP Response |\n|-------------|---------------|\n| `store.ErrNotFound` | 404 with `SessionNotFoundError` |\n| Other errors | 500 internal server error |\n\n---\n\n## Reverse Proxy Implementation\n\n### Director Function (`reverse_proxy.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc director(req *http.Request, target *url.URL, jwt string) {\n    // Path normalization\n    path := req.URL.Path\n    if path != \"\" && path[0] != '/' {\n        path = \"/\" + path\n    }\n    \n    req.URL.Scheme = target.Scheme\n    req.URL.Host = target.Host\n    req.URL.Path = path\n    req.URL.RawPath = \"\"\n    req.Host = target.Host\n    \n    // Forwarding headers\n    req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-Host\", req.Header.Get(\"Host\"))\n    proto := \"http\"\n    if req.TLS != nil {\n        proto = \"https\"\n    }\n    req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-Proto\", proto)\n    \n    existingXFF := req.Header.Get(\"X-Forwarded-For\")\n    clientIP := req.RemoteAddr\n    if existingXFF != \"\" {\n        clientIP = existingXFF + \",\" + clientIP\n    }\n    req.Header.Set(\"X-Forwarded-For\", clientIP)\n    \n    // JWT injection\n    if jwt != \"\" {\n        req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+jwt)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Entry Point Selection\n\n```go\nfunc selectEntryPoint(entryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint, invocationPath string) *types.SandboxEntryPoint {\n    if len(entryPoints) == 0 {\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    // Find matching entry point by path prefix\n    for _, ep := range entryPoints {\n        if strings.HasPrefix(invocationPath, ep.Path) {\n            return &ep\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Default to first entry point\n    return &entryPoints[0]\n}\n\nfunc buildTargetURL(ep *types.SandboxEntryPoint) *url.URL {\n    endpoint := ep.Endpoint\n    if ep.Protocol != \"\" && !strings.Contains(endpoint, \"://\") {\n        endpoint = strings.ToLower(ep.Protocol) + \"://\" + endpoint\n    }\n    return url.Parse(endpoint)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Middleware Implementation\n\n### Concurrency Limit (`middleware.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc concurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent int) gin.HandlerFunc {\n    if maxConcurrent <= 0 {\n        maxConcurrent = 1000\n    }\n    \n    sem := make(chan struct{}, maxConcurrent)\n    \n    return func(c *gin.Context) {\n        select {\n        case sem <- struct{}{}:\n            defer func() { <-sem }()\n            c.Next()\n        default:\n            c.JSON(http.StatusTooManyRequests, gin.H{\n                \"error\": \"server overloaded, please try again later\",\n                \"code\":  \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\",\n            })\n            c.Abort()\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## JWT Implementation\n\n### Token Generation (`jwt.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc (j *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n    now := time.Now()\n    \n    token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, jwt.MapClaims{\n        \"exp\": now.Add(jwtExpiration).Unix(),\n        \"iat\": now.Unix(),\n        \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n    })\n    \n    // Merge custom claims\n    for k, v := range claims {\n        token.Claims.(jwt.MapClaims)[k] = v\n    }\n    \n    return token.SignedString(j.privateKey)\n}\n```\n\n### Secret Persistence\n\n```go\nfunc (j *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error {\n    if j.clientset == nil {\n        // Try in-cluster config\n        config, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n        if err != nil {\n            klog.Warningf(\"not in cluster, skipping secret persistence: %v\", err)\n            return nil\n        }\n        j.clientset, err = kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n    }\n    \n    secret := &corev1.Secret{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      IdentitySecretName,\n            Namespace: IdentityNamespace,\n            Labels: map[string]string{\n                \"app\":       \"agentcube\",\n                \"component\": \"router\",\n            },\n        },\n        Type: corev1.SecretTypeOpaque,\n        Data: map[string][]byte{\n            PrivateKeyDataKey: encodePrivateKeyPEM(j.privateKey),\n            PublicKeyDataKey:  encodePublicKeyPEM(j.publicKey),\n        },\n    }\n    \n    _, err := j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Create(ctx, secret, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n        existing, err := j.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Get(ctx, IdentitySecretName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        return j.loadPrivateKeyPEM(existing.Data[PrivateKeyDataKey])\n    }\n    return err\n}\n```\n\n**Key Encoding:**\n- Private key: PKCS1 PEM format (`RSA PRIVATE KEY`)\n- Public key: PKIX PEM format (`PUBLIC KEY`)\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n\n| Component | Coverage Target | Key Test Cases |\n|-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n| `Server` | 80% | Construction, route registration, TLS, graceful shutdown |\n| `SessionManager` | 85% | Session resolution, Workload Manager create, error mapping |\n| `JWTManager` | 80% | Token generation, RS256 signing, secret persistence |\n| `ReverseProxy` | 85% | Director, forwarding headers, path normalization, error handler |\n| `Handlers` | 80% | Health endpoints, invocation routing, error responses |\n| `Middleware` | 75% | Concurrency limit, 429 response |\n\n### Test Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `server_test.go` | Server construction, route registration, TLS, health checks |\n| `session_manager_test.go` | GetSandboxBySession, create via Workload Manager, error cases |\n| `jwt_test.go` | Token generation, RS256 verification, secret CRUD |\n| `reverse_proxy_test.go` | Director, path normalization, header injection, error mapping |\n| `handlers_test.go` | Health endpoints, invocation handlers |\n| `middleware_test.go` | Concurrency limit, overload response |\n| `errors_test.go` | Error type construction, message formatting |\n\n### Mock Dependencies\n\n```go\ntype MockStore struct {\n    GetSandboxBySessionIDFunc  func(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandboxFunc           func(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSessionLastActivityFunc func(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n}\n\ntype MockSessionManager struct {\n    GetSandboxBySessionFunc func(ctx context.Context, sessionID, namespace, name, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\ntype MockJWTManager struct {\n    GenerateTokenFunc func(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n}\n\ntype MockHTTPClient struct {\n    DoFunc func(req *http.Request) (*http.Response, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Test Scenarios\n\n1. **Session Resolution Flow**\n   - Request without session header → creates sandbox via Workload Manager\n   - Request with valid session header → lookup from store\n   - Request with invalid session → 404 response\n\n2. **Proxy Flow**\n   - Successful proxy → response header with session ID\n   - Sandbox unreachable → 502 response\n   - Sandbox timeout → 504 response\n\n3. **JWT Injection**\n   - Sandbox/SandboxClaim kind → JWT in Authorization header\n   - AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter → no JWT\n\n4. **Concurrency Limit**\n   - Under limit → request processed\n   - At limit → 429 response\n\n5. **Graceful Shutdown**\n   - Context cancel → shutdown within 10s deadline\n   - Existing requests complete before shutdown\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Config validates required fields (Port non-empty)\n- [ ] TLS requires both cert and key when EnableTLS=true\n- [ ] SessionManager requires WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env\n- [ ] JWTManager generates valid RS256 tokens (verified by public key)\n- [ ] ReverseProxy Director normalizes paths correctly\n- [ ] ErrorHandler maps connection refused → 502\n- [ ] ErrorHandler maps timeout → 504\n- [ ] Health endpoints return correct JSON shapes\n- [ ] Concurrency middleware defaults to 1000 when config <= 0\n- [ ] Last-activity updated twice per invocation\n- [ ] Entry point selection handles empty list\n- [ ] Response header x-agentcube-session-id injected\n- [ ] Forwarding headers set correctly\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown respects 10s deadline\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **JWT Secret Rotation**: How to handle key rotation without disrupting active sessions?\n   - Proposal: Load both old and new keys, accept tokens signed by either\n\n2. **Workload Manager Retry**: Should failed sandbox creation be retried?\n   - Current: Single attempt, client must retry\n   - Alternative: Add exponential backoff retry in SessionManager\n\n3. **WebSocket Support**: Should Router proxy WebSocket upgrades?\n   - Current: Not supported (out of scope)\n   - Future: Add WebSocket upgrade handling in reverse_proxy.go\n\n4. **Metrics Export**: Prometheus metrics for proxy latency, error rates?\n   - Current: Not in scope\n   - Future: Add middleware to record request duration and status codes\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `session-routing/spec.md` — Full requirement specification\n- `session-routing/design.md` — Detailed design document  \n- `session-store/design.md` — Store interface and implementations\n- `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response types\n- `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client code reference\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` — Workload Manager server pattern reference\n- `project.md` — AgentCube architecture overview\n- Go `httputil.ReverseProxy`: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http/httputil#ReverseProxy\n- `golang-jwt/v5`: https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt\n- Gin framework: https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":60,"character":40},"end":{"line":60,"character":71}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#omitzero"},"source":"omitzero","message":"Omitempty has no effect on nested struct fields"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":49,"character":49},"end":{"line":49,"character":60}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"k8s.io/utils should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":37,"character":14},"end":{"line":37,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field WriteTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":13},"end":{"line":38,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":17},"end":{"line":39,"character":17}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field ShutdownTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":40,"character":15},"end":{"line":40,"character":15}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field EnableHealthz"},{"r